summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on Lebanon, particularly 425 (1978), 426 (1978), 1310 (2000), 1337 (2001), 1365 (2001) and 1391 (2002), 
Endorses the Secretary-General's report on UNIFIL and its recommendation to renew UNIFIL's mandate for six months; 
Extends UNIFIL's mandate until 31 January 2003; 
Requests the Secretary-General to continue implementing UNIFIL's reconfiguration; 
Reiterates support for Lebanon's territorial integrity, sovereignty and political independence; 
Commends Lebanon for deploying armed forces in the south and calls for continued measures; 
Calls for full freedom of movement for UNIFIL; 
Encourages a calm environment in the south; 
Reiterates calls on parties to respect the withdrawal line and exercise restraint; 
Condemns violence and violations, urging parties to abide by their obligations; 
Supports UNIFIL's efforts to maintain the ceasefire; 
Welcomes demining contributions and encourages further assistance; 
Requests the Secretary-General to consult with Lebanon and concerned parties; 
Requests a comprehensive report on UNIFIL's activities before the end of the mandate; 
Looks forward to the early fulfilment of UNIFIL's mandate.
Stresses the importance of achieving a comprehensive, just and lasting peace in the Middle East, based on all relevant resolutions, including resolutions 242 (1967) of 22 November 1967 and 338 (1973) of 22 October 1973.
